2. PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
Product Vision
To become a trusted, easy-to-understand digital dealership where buying a car feels safe, transparent, and stress-free.
The site should answer questions before the user asks them on WhatsApp.
USER EXPERIENCE & FLOW
Primary User Flow
A typical user journey should look like this:
User lands on homepage →
Sees cars + payment clarity →
Builds trust through proof →
Clicks WhatsApp →
Conversation continues →
Sale closes offline
No forced signups. No complex forms.
PAGE-BY-PAGE REQUIREMENTS
1. Homepage
Purpose:
First impression, trust building, and fast action.
Required Sections:
Hero Section
A large car image or short looping video.
Clear headline focused on stress-free car buying.
Headline copy example:
“Buy Your Car From EJ Without Stress – Flexible Payment Plans Available”
Primary CTAs:
• View Cars
• Chat on WhatsApp
Why Buy From Driven by EJ
Simple trust points displayed visually: • Verified cars
• Flexible payment plans
• No hidden issues
• Nationwide delivery
Featured Cars
Show 4–6 cars with: • Image
• Price
• Monthly payment teaser (“Pay from ₦___ monthly”)
• View Details button
Optional Smart Feature
A sticky notification or soft popup: “Car of the Week – Limited Offer”
2. Cars Page (Showroom Page)
Purpose:
This is the money page. Users must clearly see what’s available and how much it costs.
Each Car Card Must Show: • Clear images (front, back, interior)
• Full price
• Year, mileage, engine type
• Condition (Foreign used / Nigerian used)
• Payment option (Full / Installment)
• WhatsApp CTA button
Filters Required: • Brand (Toyota, Lexus, Mercedes, etc.)
• Budget range
• Payment type (Full / Installment)
This page should feel like browsing a clean showroom, not scrolling Instagram chaos.
3. Car Detail Page
Purpose:
Answer all questions before WhatsApp.
Required Elements: • Large image gallery
• Car specifications
• Full price
• Monthly payment estimate
• Payment options available
• Clear “Chat on WhatsApp” CTA
Optional:
Delivery availability and location note.
4. Payment Plan Page (Key Differentiator)
Purpose:
Build confidence and remove fear around installments.
Content Must Be Simple and Visual:
Explain payment structure clearly: • 50% deposit
• Balance spread: – Foreign used cars: 3–6 months
– Nigerian used cars: 2-week spread
Requirements: • Valid ID
• Signed agreement
• Any other basic requirement
Step-by-step flow: Choose a car →
Pay deposit →
Drive home →
Complete balance
No long grammar. This page should feel like a conversation, not a contract.
5. About Page
Purpose:
People buy the person, not just the car.
Required Content: • Photo of EJ or the office
• Short personal story (friendly, honest tone)
• Mission: helping people buy reliable cars without pressure or scams
Trust Proof: • Number of cars delivered
• Years of experience
• Photos of deliveries
6. Testimonials Page
Purpose:
Social proof to push undecided buyers.
Required Content: • Client photos with cars
• WhatsApp screenshot reviews
• Before/after delivery photos
Even 5 strong testimonials are enough to drive conversions.
7. Contact Page
Purpose:
Make communication effortless.
Required Elements: • WhatsApp click button (primary)
• Phone number
• Instagram link
• Optional location
No forms. No friction.
DESIGN REQUIREMENTS
Visual Style
Luxury, clean, trustworthy.
Color Palette: • Deep Navy: #0E2A3A
• Warm Gold / Mustard: #D4A437 – #C99A2E
• Off-white / Cream: #FAF7F2
• Optional accents: Slate blue or muted charcoal
Typography: • Clean, bold fonts
• Premium feel without being flashy
Layout: • Mobile-first
• Clear spacing
• Fast loading
• No heavy animations
FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
• WhatsApp chat bubble visible across site
• Click-to-chat WhatsApp CTAs everywhere
• Image optimization for speed
• SEO-friendly pages
• Easy content updates (cars, prices, testimonials)
Optional but recommended: • Installment calculator
• Blog section (education + SEO)
Blog topics: • Best first cars in Nigeria
• Foreign vs Nigerian used
• How car installments work
TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS
Frontend:
Next.js / React
Tailwind or similar styling framework
CMS / Content Management:
Simple CMS for updating: • Cars
• Prices
• Testimonials
• Blog posts
Performance:
Fast load time on low network
Optimized for mobile data users
Hosting:
Vercel or similar modern hosting platform
OUT OF SCOPE (FOR NOW)
• Online payment processing
• User accounts
• Automated checkout
All sales continue via WhatsApp.
FINAL NOTE
This website is not just a “nice design.”
It’s a sales tool, a trust builder, and a filter that brings only serious buyers into WhatsApp.